overview: The user aimed to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  adding a database for response storage and an administrative dashboard for
  data access. The assistant evaluated the existing codebase, identified missing
  components, and developed a plan. Key decisions included using NeonDB with
  Prisma for the database and implementing a simple password-based
  authentication system. The implementation involved updating demographic
  fields, creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses, developing API
  endpoints for data submission and retrieval (including CSV export), and
  building a functional admin dashboard. A significant pivot was made to
  simplify the authentication system by leveraging Next.js middleware, which
  streamlined route protection. Extensive testing confirmed that all implemented
  features were working correctly, providing a robust solution for data
  management and client access.
